com.vectorprint.report.itext.style.css

Class CssDocumentHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vectorprint.report.itext.style.css.CssDocumentHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CssToBaseStylers, org.w3c.css.sac.DocumentHandler

    public class CssDocumentHandler
extends Object
implements CssToBaseStylers
    Use an instance of this class in Parser.setDocumentHandler(org.w3c.css.sac.DocumentHandler), call Parser.parseStyleSheet(org.w3c.css.sac.InputSource). After this you can call printStylers(java.io.OutputStream) to write a stylesheet suitable for a StylerFactory.
    Author:
    Eduard Drenth at VectorPrint.nl

      • fromLexicalUnit

        public String fromLexicalUnit(org.w3c.css.sac.LexicalUnit lu)
        Description copied from interface: CssToBaseStylers
        Construct a String to use in BindingHelper.convert(java.lang.String, java.lang.Class). Probably the most messy part of the SAC api, becasue of composed css properties, because of functions for example rgb(r,g,b). It is often necessary to debug in order to find the values you need to convert to String that can be used by BindingHelper.convert(java.lang.String, java.lang.Class).
        Specified by:
        fromLexicalUnit in interface CssToBaseStylers
